      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(sessions): use account names for direct display",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n- Use configured channel account names as the display fallback for direct session rows when the current label is only an opaque direct peer id.\n- Preserve existing precedence for explicit `displayName`, session labels, group display names, and meaningful origin labels.\n- Include the account-name fallback in `sessions.list` search so users can find the readable account name.\n\nCloses #79183\n\n## Verification\n\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs run src/gateway/session-utils.test.ts src/gateway/session-utils.search.test.ts --reporter=verbose`\n- `git diff --check`\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\nBehavior addressed: Direct Feishu-style session rows show the configured channel account name instead of an opaque direct peer id when no stronger label exists, and `sessions.list` search can find that readable account name. This also covers the reviewed edge cases for non-`main` default agents and normalized account ids.\n\nReal environment tested: Local OpenClaw checkout on this PR branch (`codex/session-display-account-name-79183-20260618`) at `09347148b8893e24c44b63b0760b78f12f75822f`, exercising the actual `listSessionsFromStore` sessions.list projection path with a redacted Feishu direct-session store and channel account config.\n\nExact steps or command run after this patch:\n\n```text\nnode --import tsx -e \"import { listSessionsFromStore } from './src/gateway/session-utils.ts'; /* redacted sessions.list projection */\"\nnode scripts/run-vitest.mjs run src/gateway/session-utils.test.ts src/gateway/session-utils.search.test.ts --reporter=dot\ngit diff --check\n```\n\nEvidence after fix: Copied live output from the local redacted sessions.list projection run:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"scenario\": \"redacted sessions.list account-name fallback live output\",\n  \"all\": [\n    {\n      \"key\": \"agent:ops:feishu:direct:ou_redacted_default\",\n      \"displayName\": \"Router Display\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"key\": \"agent:quote:feishu:direct:ou_redacted_quote\",\n      \"displayName\": \"Quote Assistant\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"searchRouter\": [\n    {\n      \"key\": \"agent:ops:feishu:direct:ou_redacted_default\",\n      \"displayName\": \"Router Display\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"searchQuote\": [\n    {\n      \"key\": \"agent:quote:feishu:direct:ou_redacted_quote\",\n      \"displayName\": \"Quote Assistant\"\n    }\n  ]\n}\n```\n\nObserved result after fix: The redacted sessions.list output shows the resolved default agent `ops` using the normalized configured default account `Router D` -> `router-d` and displaying/searching as `Router Display`, while the non-default `quote` direct row still displays/searches as `Quote Assistant` before the default account fallback.\n\nWhat was not tested: No live Feishu network call was made; the proof uses redacted local persisted session data through the same gateway sessions.list projection path that formats and filters stored direct-session rows.\n\nSupplemental local checks:\n\n```text\nnode scripts/run-vitest.mjs run src/gateway/session-utils.test.ts src/gateway/session-utils.search.test.ts --reporter=dot\n\nTest Files  8 passed (8)\nTests  560 passed (560)\n[test] passed 1 Vitest shard in 42.31s\n\ngit diff --check\n```\n",
        "branch": "codex/session-display-account-name-79183-20260618",
